At this point, we should have already had a concrete agreement on the table so that it could be viewed as a horizontal one."
Vodafone concentrates its attention rather on achieving its 3G licence applications.
Miroslav Čepík adds: "We are open to negotiations of potential virtual operators, especially in the context of the sharing of expenditure and infrastructure.
We consider this, from the point of view of our customers, to be the most productive.
The main strategy of Vodafone in this area is to find a partner to build a common network for fast mobile Internet."
Competent authorities -with complicit operators
The attitude of mobile telephone operators can easily be understood, the entry of another operator would mean an increase in competition, would lead to lower prices and thus to lower profits.
Why, then, facilitate the emergence of such a competitor?
The complaints surrounding the U:fon creation testify that when operators have something they can stay on the same side.
