Today in Paris the European Equal Opportunities Summit was launched, organised this year by France with the rotating presidency of the European Union.
Lívia Járóka, Member of the European People's Party, Fidesz, in the message addressed to the plenary as the main rapporteur of the Congress, called attention to school segregation because it is the most serious legal violation affecting Roma children and, in turn, the most serious obstacle to their affirmation.
Mr Xavier Bertrand, French Minister for Employment and Social Affairs, on behalf of the French Presidency, and European Commissioner Vladimir Špidla, responsible for Employment, Social Affairs and Equal Opportunities, have opened the conference at the highest level.
