Listening to high volume music for an extended period of time using portable musical devices such as Mp3 players can cause permanent hearing injuries.
As regards the European Commission, in a communication published in Brussels, the Scientific Committee on Emergency and Recently Identified Health Risks (Csseri) of the EU, published today, draws attention to the opinion of the Scientific Committee on Health.
"From this scientific opinion - read in the note - it emerges that 5-10% of those who, for a period of at least 5 years, listen to music with portable musical devices weekly for more than one hour per day holding the device at high volume risk a permanent loss of hearing capacity."
